quarry /ˈkwɒrɪ/

(quarrying,quarried,quarries) 

1. N-COUNT A quarry is an area that is dug out from a piece of land or the side of a mountain in order to get stone or minerals. 采石场; 矿场 

例： ...an old limestone quarry. …一处老的石灰岩开采场。 

2. V-T When stone or minerals are quarried or when an area is quarried for them, they are removed from the area by digging, drilling, or using explosives. 开采; 在…处开采 

例： The large limestone caves are also quarried for cement. 这些大石灰岩洞也用来开采水泥原料。 

3. N an animal, bird, or fish that is hunted, esp by other animals; prey (被其他动物捕食的)动物、鸟或鱼 

4. N a square or diamond shape 正方形; 菱形

